title: react-native-fbsdk setup
body:
Bug report.
I am trying to do the setup for react-native-fbsdk, but it fails.

I have followed the steps given in this [link](https://github.com/facebook/react-native-fbsdk), I get the following error,

```
<Code Path>MainActivity.java:17: error: cannot find symbol
    public void onActivityResult(int requestCode, int resultCode, Intent data) {
                                                                  ^
  symbol:   class Intent
  location: class MainActivity
<Code Path>MainApplication.java:11: error: cannot find symbol
import com.facebook.CallbackManager;
                   ^
  symbol:   class CallbackManager
  location: package com.facebook
<Code Path>MainApplication.java:12: error: cannot find symbol
import com.facebook.FacebookSdk;
                   ^
  symbol:   class FacebookSdk
  location: package com.facebook
<Code Path>MainApplication.java:13: error: package com.facebook.reactnative.androidsdk does not exist
import com.facebook.reactnative.androidsdk.FBSDKPackage;
                                          ^
<Code Path>MainApplication.java:14: error: package com.facebook.appevents does not exist
import com.facebook.appevents.AppEventsLogger;
                             ^
<Code Path>MainApplication.java:21: error: cannot find symbol
  private static CallbackManager mCallbackManager = CallbackManager.Factory.create();
                 ^
  symbol:   class CallbackManager
  location: class MainApplication
<Code Path>MainApplication.java:23: error: cannot find symbol
  protected static CallbackManager getCallbackManager() {
                   ^
  symbol:   class CallbackManager
  location: class MainApplication
<Code Path>MainApplication.java:21: error: package CallbackManager does not exist
  private static CallbackManager mCallbackManager = CallbackManager.Factory.create();
                                                                   ^
<Code Path>MainApplication.java:38: error: cannot find symbol
          new FBSDKPackage(mCallbackManager)
              ^
  symbol: class FBSDKPackage
<Code Path>MainApplication.java:52: error: cannot find symbol
    FacebookSdk.sdkInitialize(getApplicationContext());
    ^
  symbol:   variable FacebookSdk
  location: class MainApplication
<Code Path>MainApplication.java:54: error: cannot find symbol
    AppEventsLogger.activateApp(this);
    ^
  symbol:   variable AppEventsLogger
  location: class MainApplication
11 errors

```

I want the installation to go successfully.

Currently I am using "16.0.0-alpha.12" version of react, I am trying this for the first time. There is no way I found in [react-native-fbsdk](https://github.com/facebook/react-native-fbsdk) to raise an issue. Hence raising here. Please help me out of this.
